  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Accordingly, since it belongs to prudence rightly to counsel, judge, and command concerning the means of obtaining a due end, it is evident that prudence regards not only the private good of the individual , but also the common good of the multitude.</data>
